runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-strategizer-step-007.log:3739:./missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-002/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:251:**Note on `sobolev_threshold.py` output:** The "critical exponent table" in that script computes the SPATIAL CZ estimate (u ∈ L^{2q} → p ∈ L^q in R^3). The GOAL's "beta = 4/3" comes from the parabolic mixed-norm estimate on Q_k (u ∈ L^{8/3}_t L^4_x → p ∈ L^{4/3}_t L^2_x → p ∈ L^{4/3}(Q_k) after Hölder). The table's "q=2 gives beta=3" is the pure spatial CZ (u ∈ L^6 → |u|^2 ∈ L^3 → p ∈ L^3 spatially), which is a different norm than the space-time L^{4/3}(Q_k). The W^{1,3} threshold conclusion is unaffected by this distinction. [CONJECTURED — the exact relationship between mixed-norm and space-time exponents in the parabolic De Giorgi setting would require more careful analysis]
